name: Transform
description:
Various lichens - primarily Orange-Cored Shadow Lichen - form patches on the base of a Birch tree, the bark peeling exposing a fresh layer within. (Phaeophyscia rubropulchra)

2020. Nikon D3500, 55-200mm Lens.

Photographed in situ, without the use of artificial lighting or staging. Photoshop only used for resizing.

1024x685 300dpi jpeg
